  "1df262e8": {
    "title": "Acetazolamide",
    "primaryType": "drug",
    "tags": [
      "Pharmacology",
      "Neurology",
      "Ophthalmology",
      "Renal",
      "USMLE"
    ],
    "classificationPath": [
      "Neurology and Special Senses",
      "Pharmacology",
      "Glaucoma Therapy"
    ],
    "content": {
      "definition": "<p><b>Acetazolamide</b> is a <i>carbonic anhydrase inhibitor</i> used as a diuretic and to reduce pressure in the eye and brain by decreasing the formation of aqueous humor and cerebrospinal fluid, respectively.</p>",
      "atAGlance": "<ul><li><b>Mechanism of Action:</b> Inhibits the enzyme carbonic anhydrase in the ciliary body epithelium and choroid plexus, which reduces the formation of bicarbonate ions (HCO<sub>3</sub><sup>-</sup>) and subsequently decreases fluid secretion (aqueous humor and CSF).</li><li><b>Clinical Use (Ophthalmology):</b> Treats [[3ce6c035|glaucoma]] (both open-angle and acute angle-closure) by <mark>decreasing aqueous humor synthesis</mark>.</li><li><b>Clinical Use (Neurology):</b> Treats [[7c4e7c74|idiopathic intracranial hypertension]] (pseudotumor cerebri) by decreasing CSF production. Also used for altitude sickness.</li><li><b>Adverse Effects:</b> Causes a <mark>hyperchloremic metabolic acidosis</mark> (non-anion gap), paresthesias, ammonia toxicity in liver disease, and promotes calcium phosphate kidney stones (due to alkalinization of urine). It is a sulfa drug, so watch for sulfa allergies.</li><li><b>USMLE Tip:</b> Remember the mnemonic 'ACID-azolamide' to recall that it causes a metabolic <b>ACID</b>osis.</li></ul>",
      "takeAway": "<p><b>Acetazolamide</b>'s therapeutic effect in both [[3ce6c035|glaucoma]] and [[7c4e7c74|idiopathic intracranial hypertension]] stems from the same core mechanism: inhibiting carbonic anhydrase to reduce the production of bicarbonate-driven fluids, namely aqueous humor and cerebrospinal fluid.</p>",
      "mermaid": "graph TD; A[Acetazolamide] --|Inhibits|--> B(Carbonic Anhydrase); B --|Blocks|--> C(H2O + CO2 <--> H2CO3 <--> H+ + HCO3-); C --|Leads to|--> D[Decreased Aqueous Humor/CSF Production];"
