  "6a005559": {
    "title": "Acetylcholine (ACh)",
    "primaryType": "molecule",
    "tags": [
      "Neuroscience",
      "Pharmacology",
      "Physiology",
      "USMLE"
    ],
    "classificationPath": [
      "Neurology and Special Senses",
      "Anatomy and Physiology",
      "Neurotransmitters"
    ],
    "content": {
      "definition": "<p><b>Acetylcholine (ACh)</b> is a major <i>excitatory neurotransmitter</i> synthesized from choline and acetyl-CoA that functions at the neuromuscular junction, in all autonomic ganglia, at parasympathetic postganglionic nerve endings, and at various sites within the central nervous system.</p>",
      "atAGlance": "<ul><li><b>Synthesis:</b> Synthesized by Choline Acetyltransferase (ChAT) from choline and acetyl-CoA.</li><li><b>Degradation:</b> Rapidly broken down in the synaptic cleft by Acetylcholinesterase (AChE) into choline and acetate.</li><li><b>CNS Role:</b> Crucial for memory and cognition. Levels are significantly decreased in [[77ae6148|Alzheimer disease]] due to degeneration of neurons in the [[361438f2|Basal nucleus of Meynert]]. Levels are also decreased in [[ffd7e743|Huntington disease]].</li><li><b>PNS Role:</b> Neurotransmitter at all preganglionic autonomic synapses (nicotinic), all parasympathetic postganglionic synapses (muscarinic), sympathetic postganglionic synapses to sweat glands (muscarinic), and the neuromuscular junction (nicotinic).</li><li><b>USMLE Tip:</b> Diseases affecting ACh are high-yield. [[77ae6148|Alzheimer's]] (‚Üì CNS ACh), Myasthenia Gravis (antibodies to ACh receptors), Lambert-Eaton (‚Üì presynaptic ACh release). Drugs targeting AChE (e.g., [[47d0372e|donepezil]]) are used to treat Alzheimer's.</li></ul>",
      "takeAway": "<p><b>Acetylcholine</b> is a versatile neurotransmitter whose function is critically dependent on its location; its depletion in the [[361438f2|Basal nucleus of Meynert]] leads to cognitive decline in [[77ae6148|Alzheimer disease]], while its blockade at the neuromuscular junction causes paralysis.</p>",
      "mermaid": "graph TD; A[Choline + Acetyl-CoA] --ChAT--> B(Acetylcholine); B --AChE--> C[Choline + Acetate]; B --> D{Receptors}; D --> D1[Nicotinic]; D --> D2[Muscarinic];"
