      "USMLE"
    ],
    "classificationPath": [
      "Neurology and Special Senses",
      "Pathology",
      "Demyelinating Disorders"
    ],
    "content": {
      "definition": "<p><b>Acute Disseminated Encephalomyelitis (ADEM)</b> is a rare, acute, <i>immune-mediated inflammatory and demyelinating disorder</i> of the central nervous system that typically occurs following a viral infection or, less commonly, a vaccination.</p>",
      "atAGlance": "<ul><li><b>Pathophysiology:</b> Believed to be caused by <mark>molecular mimicry</mark>, where an immune response against an infectious agent cross-reacts with myelin antigens (e.g., myelin basic protein).</li><li><b>Clinical Presentation:</b> Rapid onset of multifocal neurological symptoms, including encephalopathy (altered mental status, confusion, coma), which is a key feature distinguishing it from a typical [[45dd6d19|Multiple Sclerosis]] flare. Other symptoms include fever, headache, seizures, and focal deficits.</li><li><b>Timing:</b> Symptoms typically appear 1-2 weeks after an antecedent infection (e.g., measles, varicella) or vaccination.</li><li><b>Imaging:</b> MRI shows multiple, bilateral, asymmetric, poorly demarcated white matter lesions of similar age, often involving both the brain and spinal cord.</li><li><b>USMLE Tip:</b> Differentiate ADEM from [[45dd6d19|MS]]: ADEM is <u>monophasic</u> and presents with encephalopathy, whereas MS is typically relapsing-remitting and rarely presents with encephalopathy in its initial flare.</li></ul>",
      "takeAway": "<p><b>Acute Disseminated Encephalomyelitis</b> is a post-infectious autoimmune attack on CNS myelin, distinguished from [[45dd6d19|Multiple Sclerosis]] by its <u>monophasic</u> course and the prominent presence of encephalopathy alongside multifocal neurological deficits.</p>",
      "mermaid": "graph TD; A[Viral Infection/Vaccination] --> B(Immune Response); B --Molecular Mimicry--> C[Attack on Myelin]; C --> D[Perivenous Inflammation & Demyelination]; D --> E[Multifocal Neurologic Deficits + Encephalopathy];"
    },
    "connections": [
