    "content": {
      "definition": "<p><b>Adrenoleukodystrophy</b> is an <i>X-linked recessive disorder</i> caused by a mutation in the <b>ABCD1</b> gene, leading to impaired Œ≤-oxidation of very-long-chain fatty acids (VLCFAs) in peroxisomes. This results in the accumulation of VLCFAs in the adrenal glands, testes, and white matter of the brain, causing adrenal insufficiency and progressive demyelination.</p>",
      "atAGlance": "<ul><li><b>Genetics:</b> X-linked recessive mutation in the <i>ABCD1</i> gene.</li><li><b>Pathophysiology:</b> Defective peroxisomal Œ≤-oxidation leads to the accumulation of <mark>very-long-chain fatty acids (VLCFAs)</mark> in various tissues.</li><li><b>Neurologic Manifestations:</b> Progressive demyelination of the central nervous system, leading to cognitive decline, behavioral changes, spasticity, and vision/hearing loss.</li><li><b>Endocrine Manifestations:</b> Adrenal insufficiency ([[addison_disease|Addison disease]]) is a common feature, presenting with fatigue, hyperpigmentation, and electrolyte abnormalities. Testicular atrophy and infertility can also occur.</li><li><b>USMLE Tip:</b> A classic vignette involves a young boy with new-onset behavioral problems or declining school performance who also shows signs of adrenal insufficiency (e.g., hyperpigmentation, low cortisol).</li></ul>",
      "takeAway": "<p><b>Adrenoleukodystrophy</b> is a dual-system disease combining progressive CNS demyelination with adrenal failure, all stemming from a single X-linked genetic defect in peroxisomal fatty acid metabolism.</p>",
      "mermaid": "graph TD; A[ABCD1 Gene Mutation] --> B(Defective Peroxisomal Œ≤-oxidation); B --> C[Accumulation of VLCFAs]; C --> D[Adrenal Cortex] --> E(Adrenal Insufficiency); C --> F[CNS White Matter] --> G(Demyelination & Neurodegeneration);"
