      "Neurology and Special Senses",
      "Anatomy and Physiology",
      "Meninges"
    ],
    "content": {
      "definition": "<p>The <b>Arachnoid Mater</b> is the middle layer of the three meninges that surround the brain and spinal cord. It is a delicate, avascular membrane located between the outer [[5bbe3597|dura mater]] and the inner [[pia_mater|pia mater]].</p>",
      "atAGlance": "<ul><li><b>Structure:</b> Composed of a web-like network of collagen and elastic fibers, from which it gets its name (from Greek 'arachne' for spider).</li><li><b>Embryologic Origin:</b> Derived from the [[14c6f2a7|neural crest]].</li><li><b>Subarachnoid Space:</b> The space between the arachnoid mater and the pia mater is the <mark>subarachnoid space</mark>, which contains cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) and major cerebral blood vessels.</li><li><b>Arachnoid Granulations:</b> Protrusions of the arachnoid mater through the dura into the superior sagittal sinus, responsible for CSF reabsorption.</li><li><b>Clinical Relevance:</b> Rupture of an artery in the subarachnoid space (e.g., from a berry aneurysm) causes a [[63f8b05f|subarachnoid hemorrhage]]. A [[e98ea0ba|meningioma]], a common benign brain tumor, arises from arachnoid cap cells.</li></ul>",
      "takeAway": "<p>The <b>Arachnoid Mater</b> forms a crucial boundary, creating the subarachnoid space that houses the CSF and cerebral vasculature, and its specialized granulations are essential for CSF drainage.</p>",
      "mermaid": "graph TD; A[Skull] --> B[Dura Mater]; B --> C(Arachnoid Mater); C --> D[Subarachnoid Space - CSF]; D --> E[Pia Mater]; E --> F[Brain];"
    },
