  "c335e16d": {
    "title": "Basement Membrane (CNS)",
    "primaryType": "anatomy",
    "tags": [
      "Neuroanatomy",
      "Histology",
      "Physiology",
      "USMLE"
    ],
    "classificationPath": [
      "Neurology and Special Senses",
      "Anatomy and Physiology",
      "Blood-Brain Barrier"
    ],
    "content": {
      "definition": "<p>In the central nervous system, the <b>basement membrane</b> is a thin, specialized layer of the extracellular matrix that surrounds cerebral capillaries and, along with astrocyte foot processes and endothelial tight junctions, forms a critical component of the [[dd47b9cc|blood-brain barrier]].</p>",
      "atAGlance": "<ul><li><b>Composition:</b> Primarily composed of Type IV collagen, laminin, and proteoglycans.</li><li><b>Function:</b> Provides structural support to the capillary endothelium and acts as a selective filter, regulating the passage of molecules from the blood into the brain parenchyma.</li><li><b>Role in Blood-Brain Barrier:</b> The basement membrane, together with endothelial [[tight_junctions|tight junctions]] and astrocyte end-feet, creates the highly restrictive [[dd47b9cc|blood-brain barrier]].</li><li><b>Pathology:</b> Thickening of the basement membrane is a feature of chronic hyperglycemia in diabetes, contributing to microvascular complications like [[73b00ab0|diabetic retinopathy]]. In [[goodpasture_syndrome|Goodpasture syndrome]], autoantibodies target Type IV collagen in the basement membranes of the kidneys and lungs.</li><li><b>USMLE Tip:</b> The three key components of the blood-brain barrier are: 1) Tight junctions between non-fenestrated endothelial cells, 2) The basement membrane, and 3) Astrocyte foot processes.</li></ul>",
      "takeAway": "<p>The <b>basement membrane</b> of CNS capillaries is a crucial structural and functional element of the [[dd47b9cc|blood-brain barrier]], acting as both scaffolding and a selective filter to maintain the tightly controlled environment of the brain.</p>",
      "mermaid": ""
    },
    "connections": [
      {
        "type": "is_a_component_of",
        "to": "dd47b9cc"
      },
      {
        "type": "is_composed_of",
        "to": "type_iv_collagen"
      },
      {
        "type": "is_thickened_in",
        "to": "diabetes_mellitus"
      }
    ]
