  "a9f6d703": {
    "title": "Berry Aneurysm",
    "primaryType": "disease",
    "tags": [
      "Neurology",
      "Neurosurgery",
      "Pathology",
      "USMLE"
    ],
    "classificationPath": [
      "Neurology and Special Senses",
      "Pathology",
      "Cerebrovascular Disease"
    ],
    "content": {
      "definition": "<p>A <b>Berry Aneurysm</b>, also known as a saccular aneurysm, is a thin-walled, sac-like outpouching of a cerebral artery, typically located at arterial branch points within the [[e22300e8|Circle of Willis]]. Its rupture is the most common cause of non-traumatic [[63f8b05f|subarachnoid hemorrhage]].</p>",
      "atAGlance": "<ul><li><b>Location:</b> Most commonly found at the junction of the [[bd802d22|anterior communicating artery (AComA)]] with the anterior cerebral artery. The second most common site is the junction of the posterior communicating artery (PComA) with the internal carotid artery.</li><li><b>Pathophysiology:</b> Believed to form due to a congenital weakness in the vessel wall (lack of tunica media) at arterial bifurcations, which is exacerbated over time by hemodynamic stress from hypertension.</li><li><b>Associated Conditions:</b> Increased incidence in patients with <mark>Autosomal Dominant Polycystic Kidney Disease (ADPKD)</mark>, Ehlers-Danlos syndrome, and Marfan syndrome.</li><li><b>Clinical Presentation:</b> Usually asymptomatic until rupture. Rupture causes a [[63f8b05f|subarachnoid hemorrhage]], presenting with a sudden, explosive <mark>\"worst headache of my life.\"</mark></li><li><b>USMLE Tip:</b> A PComA aneurysm can compress the ipsilateral [[68c66997|oculomotor nerve (CN III)]], causing a painful third nerve palsy with a dilated, nonreactive pupil ('blown pupil'). This is a neurosurgical emergency.</li></ul>",
      "takeAway": "<p><b>Berry aneurysms</b> are silent vascular time bombs located at the branch points of the Circle of Willis; their rupture leads to a devastating subarachnoid hemorrhage, classically presenting as a 'thunderclap headache'.</p>",
      "mermaid": "graph TD; A[Arterial Bifurcation in Circle of Willis] --> B(Congenital Wall Weakness); B --Hypertension--> C(Berry Aneurysm Formation); C --> D{Rupture}; D --> E[Subarachnoid Hemorrhage];"
    },
    "connections": [
