  "03ba9967": {
    "title": "Blood-Nerve Barrier",
    "primaryType": "anatomy",
    "tags": [
      "Neuroanatomy",
      "Histology",
      "Physiology",
      "USMLE"
    ],
    "classificationPath": [
      "Neurology and Special Senses",
      "Anatomy and Physiology",
      "Peripheral Nervous System"
    ],
    "content": {
      "definition": "<p>The <b>Blood-Nerve Barrier</b> is a physiological barrier in the peripheral nervous system that regulates the passage of substances from the blood into the endoneurial space, maintaining a stable microenvironment for peripheral nerve fibers.</p>",
      "atAGlance": "<ul><li><b>Structure:</b> The main cellular component is the <mark>perineurium</mark>, which consists of layers of flattened perineurial cells joined by tight junctions. Tight junctions between endothelial cells of the endoneurial capillaries also contribute.</li><li><b>Function:</b> Protects peripheral nerves from toxins, pathogens, and inflammatory cells, similar to the role of the [[dd47b9cc|blood-brain barrier]] in the CNS.</li><li><b>Comparison to BBB:</b> While analogous to the BBB, the blood-nerve barrier is generally considered less restrictive.</li><li><b>Pathology:</b> Breakdown of the blood-nerve barrier is a key feature of inflammatory neuropathies like [[ed52e40b|Guillain-Barr√© syndrome]]. This breakdown allows inflammatory cells and proteins to enter the endoneurial space, leading to demyelination and axonal damage.</li><li><b>USMLE Tip:</b> The breakdown of the blood-nerve barrier in [[ed52e40b|Guillain-Barr√© syndrome]] explains the classic CSF finding of [[a0f3ce4c|albuminocytologic dissociation]]‚Äîhigh protein (leaking from the blood) with a normal cell count.</li></ul>",
      "takeAway": "<p>The <b>Blood-Nerve Barrier</b>, formed primarily by the tight junctions of the perineurium, serves as the protective gatekeeper for peripheral nerves; its disruption in inflammatory conditions like Guillain-Barr√© syndrome allows an autoimmune assault on the nerves.</p>",
      "mermaid": ""
    },
    "connections": [
      {
        "type": "is_analogous_to",
        "to": "dd47b9cc"
      },
