  "869535a9": {
    "title": "Bone Morphogenetic Protein (BMP)",
    "primaryType": "molecule",
    "tags": [
      "Embryology",
      "Neuroscience",
      "Developmental Biology",
      "USMLE"
    ],
    "classificationPath": [
      "Neurology and Special Senses",
      "Embryology",
      "Neural Development"
    ],
    "content": {
      "definition": "<p><b>Bone Morphogenetic Proteins (BMPs)</b> are a group of growth factors belonging to the transforming growth factor-beta (TGF-Œ≤) superfamily. In neuroembryology, they play a crucial role in establishing the dorsal-ventral axis of the neural tube by inducing the development of the dorsal structures.</p>",
      "atAGlance": "<ul><li><b>Function in Neurodevelopment:</b> Secreted by the overlying ectoderm, BMPs act as a signaling molecule that patterns the dorsal neural tube.</li><li><b>Dorsalization:</b> High concentrations of BMPs induce the formation of the <mark>[[43be7a6e|alar plate]]</mark>, which gives rise to sensory neurons in the dorsal horn of the spinal cord and sensory nuclei of the brainstem.</li><li><b>Counterpart Signal:</b> The ventralizing signal is <mark>Sonic Hedgehog (SHH)</mark>, which is secreted by the notochord and induces the formation of the [[253e3efb|basal plate]] (motor neurons).</li><li><b>Gradient Effect:</b> The opposing gradients of BMP (high dorsally) and SHH (high ventrally) establish the distinct sensory (dorsal) and motor (ventral) domains of the developing central nervous system.</li><li><b>USMLE Tip:</b> Remember the source and effect: BMP from the ectoderm (roof) induces the dorsal/sensory alar plate. SHH from the notochord (floor) induces the ventral/motor basal plate.</li></ul>",
      "takeAway": "<p><b>Bone Morphogenetic Protein</b> acts as the key 'dorsalizing' signal in the developing neural tube, instructing the dorsal region to become the sensory [[43be7a6e|alar plate]], thereby establishing the fundamental sensory-motor polarity of the central nervous system in opposition to the ventralizing signal, Sonic Hedgehog.</p>",
      "mermaid": "graph TD; A[Ectoderm] --Secretes--> B(BMPs); B --Induces--> C(Dorsal Neural Tube); C --> D(Alar Plate); D --> E(Sensory Neurons);"
    },
    "connections": [
