  "7f6ed344": {
    "title": "Broca's Aphasia",
    "primaryType": "finding",
    "tags": [
      "Neurology",
      "Pathology",
      "Stroke",
      "USMLE"
    ],
    "classificationPath": [
      "Neurology and Special Senses",
      "Pathology",
      "Aphasia"
    ],
    "content": {
      "definition": "<p><b>Broca's aphasia</b>, also known as expressive aphasia, is a language disorder characterized by difficulty in producing fluent, grammatical speech, while comprehension remains relatively intact. It is caused by a lesion in [[a3bbace2|Broca's area]].</p>",
      "atAGlance": "<ul><li><b>Lesion Location:</b> <mark>Inferior frontal gyrus</mark> of the dominant (usually left) hemisphere.</li><li><b>Vascular Supply:</b> Supplied by the superior division of the [[143bb23d|Middle Cerebral Artery (MCA)]].</li><li><b>Clinical Presentation:</b> Speech is <mark>nonfluent, telegraphic, and effortful</mark>. Patients use short phrases and omit functional words (e.g., \"Walk dog\"). Repetition is impaired.</li><li><b>Comprehension:</b> Auditory and reading comprehension are relatively preserved, although complex grammar may be difficult.</li><li><b>Patient Awareness:</b> Patients are typically aware of their deficits and become very frustrated by their inability to communicate effectively.</li><li><b>USMLE Tip:</b> Mnemonic: <b>B</b>roca's is <b>B</b>roken <b>B</b>oca (mouth). Look for a patient with a right hemiparesis (especially face and arm) who can follow commands but struggles to speak in complete sentences.</li></ul>",
      "takeAway": "<p><b>Broca's aphasia</b> is a disorder of language production, not comprehension, resulting from damage to the brain's motor-speech planning center. The resulting speech is broken and effortful, leaving the patient frustratingly aware of their inability to express their intact thoughts.</p>",
      "mermaid": "graph TD; A[Lesion in Broca's Area] --> B(Impaired Speech Production); B --> C(Nonfluent, Telegraphic Speech); A --Spares--> D(Wernicke's Area); D --> E(Intact Comprehension);"
    },
    "connections": [
